news.title: Ansal Housing posts net loss of Rs 12.78 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: Ansal Housing's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 57.69 crore, a growth of 95 per cent from Rs 29.58 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: European Central Bank can't ignore developing housing bubble: Isabel Schnabel
news.para: House prices are rising quickly across much of the euro zone and low interest rates, combined with a particularly high savings rate, has led to a surge in property investments, especially among the bloc's wealthiest households.

news.title: Puravankara sells its subsidiary for Rs 9.27 crore
news.para: Puravankara has also received the outstanding amount of approx. Rs 35 crore from Nile Developers.

news.title: Berger Paints India posts net profit of Rs 219.21 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: Berger Paints India's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 2,238 crore, a growth of 27 per cent from Rs 1,765.73 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram corporation to conduct property tax adalat from Nov 22
news.para: The city corporation will organise a month long tax adalat here to address issues regarding property tax payment in the city following allegations of fund fraud in zonal offices.

news.title: Investors await Evergrande's overdue $148 million payment as debt woes grow
news.para: Evergrande has not defaulted on any of its offshore debt obligations, but another overdue $148 million bond payment must be made on Wednesday and it has coupon payments totalling more than $255 million on its June 2023 and 2025 bonds on Dec. 28.

news.title: Birla Corporation's net profit dips 49% to Rs 85.50 crore Q2 FY22
news.para: Birla Corporation's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,711.10 crore, a growth of 2 per cent from Rs 1,675.41 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: UCO Bank enters co-lending agreement with Aadhar Housing Finance
news.para: ​​The partnership aims at providing easy and convenient home finance solutions to customers from the economically weaker sections of society, he said.

news.title: Dubai: Union Properties' chairman dismissed from company's board
news.para: Khalifa Hassan al-Hammadi, who had served as chairman of the board of directors of Union Properties, and three other board members were dismissed, leaving in place just three of the company's seven board members.

news.title: India Cements' net profit dips 57% to Rs 32.53 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: India Cements' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 1,241.44 crore, a growth of 13 per cent from Rs 1,094.58 crore it registered in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Residents of 27 villages protest against property tax hike by Kalyan-Dombivli civic body
news.para: The protest was led by 27 Ganv Sangharsh Samiti president Gangaram Shelar and vice president Gulab Vaze. Vaze said that after 27 villages were included in KDMC, they have increased property tax at least 10 times but have not given any services in these villages.

news.title: Embassy Group to develop commercial space in Bengaluru
news.para: Located along the Sankey Road, Embassy Zenith will come up on a total area of 2.27 acres and a total leasable area of approximately 5.5 lakh sq ft. Mac Charles (India) will project manage the development which will be designed by Andy Fisher Workshop from Singapore.

news.title: Construction waste to be collected in Jaipur soon
news.para: According to an estimate, every day around 300 metric tons of CND waste is generated here that is dumped on the roadside.

news.title: Saint-Gobain acquires minority stake in Livspace
news.para: Livspace had recently said that it plans to invest $50 million to expand its business across 80 markets including 60 new market entries across India and 20 Asia Pacific cities.

news.title: Punjab cabinet approves Rs 5.50 per cubic ft rates for sand, gravel
news.para: ​​According to the policy, sand and gravel will be provided to the public at Rs 5.5 per cubic feet at mining sites, including loading charges. ​​Further, the royalty rate of ordinary clay and ordinary earth shall be decreased from Rs 10 per tonne to Rs 2.50 per tonne.
